{
  "text": "Finally, these interviewees pointed to a number of issues that may facilitate the implementation of genetic testing in the mainstream: more effective communication, particularly across specialities, identification of mainstreaming champions and more comprehensive guidelines/educational support for those in mainstream specialities [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . These suggestions confirm earlier observations made by those involved in piloting mainstreamed services in the UK [CITATION_3] and Australia [CITATION_4] , and reflect earlier experiences at the study site.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "19254941",
